I just finished reading the fourth Tales of the Otori book! I can't believe it! That was so incredible tragic!!

<lj-cut text="Spoilers">
It's impossible! When Taku died, I imagined that the ending would not be a happily ever afting... but I still can't believe that Kaede betrayed Takeo!! How could she!?!

And I was a Hiroshi x Shigeko fan! Why? Why?? Takeo promised her that she would be able to marry him! She should have!! WHY!?! (Well, actually I understand why, I'm not stupid... but it's so unfair anyway.)

And it's never revealed what happened to Ishida (though, let's be honest, it's all his fault)... and I would have loved to see Hiroshi actually at Terayama in the end... ;_;

I want a book 5 with Saga dying and Hiroshi getting married with Shigeko!! *SULKS*

Which Yaoi Series Are You?

Your series is Loveless, the tale of a boy named Ritsuka trying to find out the truth behind his older brother's murder. He is entirely alone until a young man named Soubi appears and says he knew his brother, and, whatmore, Ritsuka will now be taking his brother's place as Soubi's fighting partner. This series is overload on the angst, with the question of "who am I?" brought up at every possible opportunity, and Soubi's relationship with Ritsuka is practically servant-master, leading to abuse and thus more angst. Unfinished though the series is, its nonstop creativity is addictive - from the battles to how children have cat ears and tails that they loose when they become an adult (physically, if you know what I mean *wink wink*), there's always something new and unique. This is the series for fans of fun, reflective, philosophizing angst.

I know that some of you are getting HP as soon as it hits the stores. I am not. I'll have to wait until Sole finishes it and then ask her for the book.

So, please... DON'T GIVE SPOILERS! If you want to comment on your journal how sad you were because xx died, or how unexpected was something, or anything... use the lj-cut tag! PLEASE!!

It was bad enough knowing about the hacker who said <lj-cut text="this is how you use a lj-cut, you see?">that Hermione and Hagrid die.</lj-cut> But I chose not to believe it, and I don't want spoilers letting me know if it was true or false. I don't want to know anything until I read it myself!

I'll be asking for this again when the book finally comes out (this saturday, if I'm not wrong). Please, think of poor Merc-chan before commenting anything. PLEASE!!

Last night I went to the cinema with Sole-chan. We watched Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix. It was great!

<lj-cut text="Spoilers under the cut...">
The best scene is probably the leaving of the Weasley twins from Hogwarts. It was great and up to the expectations.
The scene that really disappointed me was Sirius' death. I was so ready to die, and then it was... "That's all? He died already?" Though the scene that followed with Harry yelling and Remus grabbing him it was EXACTLY how I imagined it when I read the book.
The scene I totally missed (and I really wanted to see it) is when Umbridge and the four aurors attack McGonagall. But, oh, well... not everything can make it to the big screen.
Ron was adorable. I think they showed him so much mature than in the books (I've always thought he's the character who has grown the less). The Ron and Hermione scenes were so cute also.
I liked how they incorporated flashbacks from the previous movies. And talking about flashbacks, the whole Snape getting mad scene was so stupid. Harry was supposed to watch his memories while defending himself, that's why Snape used the pensieve, and that's why it was so wrong that Harry peeked on the pensieve. But here they showed it as Harry defending himself and accidentally watching Snape's memories and Snape getting mad.
Another thing, poor Cho! I mean, I never liked the girl, me being a Harry x Ginny fan. But here they really made her a bitch. I mean, betraying the DA?? That's low!
Grawp was nice. And the centaurs were much better than Firenze in the first movie.
Imelda Staunton as Dolores Umbridge, WONDERFUL! Such a great performance.

Sirius: Get away from my godson! *punches Lucius in the face*
Merc: *gets all heartshape-eyed in the cinema*

Oh! And Remus x Sirius. There were two scenes at the beginning. So romantic... ^^
</lj-cut>

Presents... I love presents... they don't need to be expensive... I just love to think that someone remembered me and wasted time in buying a present... or made a present for me by themselves... ^^ Today my mom woke me up singing the birthday tune. She was bringing me breakfast to bed. I love to take breakfast on bed! ^^ Then she gave me her present. Jewelry! ^^ And beautiful! Yesterday, I received a MitKo banner/e-card from . It was beautiful and personalized! I liked it very much! ^^ And last friday I went to watch PotC 3 with Sole-chan and she gave me her present. It's a Mokona plushie! And she made it all by herself! POO!! ^_____________^ Btw, today my mom will be cooking lasagna for me. She hasn't cooked lasagna in years. I am so happy! ^^ And tomorrow we'll go to my gramps' house and my aunts will be buying chinese food. I love chinese food. ^^ I'll be rambling later about this year's importance and all that... -.- Later...

Last night I went to watch Pirates of the Caribbean 3 with Sole-chan. Great movie! Sadly, it's not as comic as the previous ones, but its action scenes are wonderful. The Sparrows aparitions turn a little repetitive at the end, but Jack continues being the genius he is. The end is perfect. I couldn't have imagined a better ending for the trilogy. I'd give 9/10 to this movie! ^^
